<img src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Powwow-with-E’.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="720" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-883475 lazyload" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Powwow-with-E’.jpg 1280w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Powwow-with-E’-640x360.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Powwow-with-E’-1062x598.jpg 1062w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Powwow-with-E’-320x180.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Powwow-with-E’-281x158.jpg 281w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Powwow-with-E’-562x316.jpg 562w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Powwow-with-E’-531x299.jpg 531w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Powwow-with-E’-487x274.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Powwow-with-E’-974x548.jpg 974w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Powwow-with-E’-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" />Powwow with E’ is a Fruitful Hangout for Stay-at-Home moms hosted by Eziaha Bolaji-Olojo (the Visioner) which holds about 4 times a year. The purpose of these meetings is to speak strength to, and help moms not only fully immerse but also find joy and be fruitful in this season as a Stay at home mom. It was born from the personal struggles and eventual victory of the visioner, and is a means of giving back to her Sisters and fellow stay at home moms. This December, we shall be hosting 100 stay at home moms, (Domestic Queens) to the final hangout for the year tagged FINISH STRONG, START STRONGER. Ten speakers will be present at this full day hangout covering such topics as Making work at homework, Godly and Strategic parenting, Getting back into the Corporate world, maximizing your 24-hour day, Raising a FIT Family, Managing your domestic helps, Managing the household finances and more. Among our Speakers are Udochi Muogilim, Partner/Senior Manager at Pricewaterhouse Coopers (PwC), Funto Ibuoye, Convener, Becoming Conference, Farida Ladipo-Ajayi, CEO/Founder Bookworm café, Mofolusade Sonaike, Founder Mumpreneur.ng and more. Various confirmed sponsors have graciously partnered with us to also ensure that every Domestic Queen goes home with a gift, including Zaron Cosmetics, Laterna Books, Reel Fruits, GazMadu Photography and more. The event will hold on Tuesday, December 4, 2018 from 9am. It is free but registration is compulsory and will shut down once 100 Queens have signed up. Please send an email to powwow@eziaha.com and follow our page on Instagram @stayhomemoms.ng for more details. 